Peru Stocks: Alicorp, Atacocha, IRL, Maple, Relapasa, Volcan

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-03-30T21:27:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/peru-stocks-alicorp-atacocha-irl-maple-relapasa-volcan.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:11 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima  General Index rose 1.5 percent to 21,807.64. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index advanced 1.2 percent to 2,910.11.  Fuel refiners gained after natural gas futures rebounded in
New York, said Arlen Lahura, a trader at Lima-based brokerage
Coril SAB.  Maple Energy Plc. (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, rose 4.2 percent to 99 cents.
Refineria la Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of Spain’s Repsol
YPF SA, gained 2.7 percent to 1.91 soles.  Gold and silver miners rose after futures advanced in New
York.  Volcan Cia Minera SAA (VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s largest silver
producer, gained 3.1 percent to 3.98 soles. Cia. Minera Atacocha
SA (ATACOBC1 PE), the Lima-based silver and zinc producer, rose
3.3 percent to 1.27 soles.  Minera IRL Ltd. (MIRL)  , a U.K.
minerals explorer with a gold mine in Peru, gained 2 percent to
$1.51.  Alicorp SA (ALICORC1)  (ALICORC1 PE), Peru’s largest foodstuff maker,
rose 4.9 percent to 5.35 soles. The company said it plans to
build a pet food plant in  China , the Gestion newspaper in Lima
reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  